\newlabel{fig:floor}{{11}{35}{No-LoRA floor control. (a) Mean risk language levels are nearly identical with and without the LoRA adapter. (b) Between-agent variance is $2.44\times $ higher with LoRA adapters. The adapter's contribution is individual differentiation, not mean-level risk}{figure.11}{}}
